WARNING:HOTPLUG_SECTION: Using __devinit is unnecessary
#84: FILE: drivers/input/serio/q40kbd.c:119:
+static int __devinit q40kbd_probe(struct platform_device *dev)

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*q40kbd_port)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct serio)...)
#87: FILE: drivers/input/serio/q40kbd.c:121:
+	q40kbd_port = kzalloc(sizeof(struct serio), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

